### <span id="v.LXXIV-p1.1"></span>CHAPTER LXXIV.

<span id="v.LXXIV-p2"></span>

<span id="v.LXXIV-p3"></span>The supreme Being is to be hoped for.

<span id="v.LXXIV-p4"></span>

<span id="v.LXXIV-p5"></span>BUT the human soul will by no means be able
to train itself in this purpose, if it despairs of being able to reach
what it aims at. Hence, devotion to effort is not more profitable to it
than hope of attainment is necessary.

